The paper proposes a machine learning method for identifying multi-line outages in power transmission networks in real time. This involves solving a computationally hard problem, which suggests that the paper may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The method is based on Monte Carlo simulations, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of labeled data for training, which suggests that it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with power transmission networks, which suggests that it may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
